{"questionId":"9076389","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Rhodium-106 (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"_{\\,\\,\\,45}^{106}{\\text{Rh}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi></mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mn>45</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>106</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Rh</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>)&nbsp;decays into palladium-106 (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"_{\\,\\,\\,46}^{106}{\\text{Pd}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi></mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mn>46</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>106</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Pd</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>)&nbsp;by beta minus (<em>β</em><sup>–</sup>) decay.</p>\n<p>The binding energy per nucleon of rhodium is 8.521 MeV and that of palladium&nbsp;is 8.550 MeV.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the energy released in the <em>β</em><sup>–</sup> decay of rhodium is about 3 MeV.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Q</em>&nbsp;= 106 × 8.550 − 106 × 8.521 = 3.07&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>MeV<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong><em>Q&nbsp;</em>≈ 3&nbsp;Me V<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076389","referenceCode":"18M.2.SL.TZ2.6b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that the energy released in the β– decay of rhodium is about 3 MeV.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 7: Atomic, nuclear and particle physics","7.2 – Nuclear reactions","Core","Topic 7: Atomic, nuc